\textbf{\MakeUppercase{Part 1: Equilibrium around center of mass}}\\
Balance a two-meter stick by hanging it near its center.  Place mass $m_1=500\mbox{ g}$ on the 75~cm mark and do not move that mass. Make the stick balance by placing another mass, $m_2$, at a different location. Use five different masses for $m_2$ and for each one find the distance $L$ shown in the figure below.

\begin{figure}[h]
\begin{center}
\includegraphics[]{./centerofmass}
\end{center}
\end{figure}

